We recommended that management:
Require the LDRRMO to submit the required LDRRMFIP in a standard format as prescribed in the above cited Circular;
Require the LDRRMO to incorporate all expenditures of programs, projects and activities in the LDRRMFIP as required including the expenditures chargeable under the special trust fund, infrastructure projects of the LDRRMF and the unforeseen/unplanned expenditures;
Revise regularly the LDRRMFIP upon approval by proper authorities the work and financial plan of the LDRRMF for any unforeseen/unplanned expenditures to be added therein.

We recommended that the City Government thru the City-ENRD to provide technical and financial assistance to the concern seventy nine (79) barangays on the following requirements as mandated under City Ordinance 2007-182 for an efficient and effective collection and disposal of solid waste to mitigate health and environmental risks, as follows:

1. Creation of Barangay Ecological Solid Waste Management Committee (BESWMC) of the remaining eleven (11) barangays;

2.Construction of  Material Recovery Facilities of the remaining ten (10) barangays and composting area of the remaining sixteen (16) barangays;

3.Submission of monthly report to the City Ecological Solid Waste Management Board (CESWMB) on the SWM implementation and furnish copy of the report to the City DILG office; and

4. Submission of their 10-year solid waste management plan to the city solid waste management for review and consolidation into its 10-year solid waste management plan.

We recommended that management:

1.Require the end-users to meticulously plan and submit a detailed PPMP to the BAC for easy consolidation in the Annual Procurement Plan;

2.Require the BAC to prepare the Consolidated Annual Procurement Plan (APP) on the prescribed format from the GPPB;

3.Refrain from splitting requisitions and contracts and adhere strictly to the provisions of R.A. 9184 and its Revised IRR-A.

Require the concerned offices to process with dispatch the DVs pertaining to payment of supplies and materials in order to attain the timely recognition of inventories after delivery of said items;  


Instruct the GSO to coordinate with the CAO in giving priority to the payment of deliveries immediately after the acceptance of goods; and



Moreover, observed the use of routing slip to ascertain the time the documents stayed on each department and monitor its location.
